In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims May 2012 as Older Americans Month. He recognizes the valuable contributions that older Americans make to society and encourages them to stay engaged and active. The theme for this year's Older Americans Month is "Never Too Old to Play." The article also mentions Senior Corps Week, which celebrates the service of over 300,000 Senior Corps volunteers. The Obama Administration is working to support older Americans in staying healthy, independent, and engaged through initiatives such as strengthening Medicare, protecting Social Security, and implementing the Affordable Care Act. The Department of Health and Human Services has awarded grants to ensure the health and independence of older adults, and the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau is working to protect them from financial schemes. The article concludes by calling upon all Americans to acknowledge and appreciate the contributions of older Americans during this month and throughout the year.